The activity of developing a AAL Platform plugin. This is done in a specific project template that has the necessary libraries and settings pre-configured. While the process in many ways is similar to that of developing AAL applications, the set of tools to use, the templates to start from, and the result is different. During this activity, the developer will usually make use of the platform source code either to enhance existing components or to debug the plugin under development. The result will typically be a component that either replaces or updates one of the middleware components, or a new component that adds additional functionality to the platform.

UML:TaggedValue.value: During the deployment procedure the uStore can request some tests to be run by a testing server in order to certify if the whole AAL application meets some important requirements.

Developer publishes or updates the application for the Service Provider:
  1. uStore (or manually the user accessing the uStore) can invoke the Testing Server's API in order to run one or more tests. run_test(...) API (the name could be renamed in the future) let the actor specify the set of Targets to be tested. The Testing Server produces some kind of result (here expressed as Result obj) necessary in order to add the certificate the application.
  2. uStore (or manually the user accessing the uStore) can run the tests by specifying the Target. The Result obj is necessary to add the certificate the application

1. Developer writes code or models applications
  2. Developer runs some tests within the AAL Studio
  3. AAL Studio can exploit inner tools in order to run the tests or interact with the Testing Server in order to lunch the tests
  4. AAL Studio sends a report to the developer by means of (e.g) alert on the test Eclipse perspective or on the web-based user interface.
